{"id": "EUVD-2025-20418", "enisaUuid": "4413631c-458d-31b9-b716-937210a2a174", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nmedia: platform: exynos4-is: Add hardware sync wait to fimc_is_hw_change_mode()\n\nIn fimc_is_hw_change_mode(), the function changes camera modes without\nwaiting for hardware completion, risking corrupted data or system hangs\nif subsequent operations proceed before the hardware is ready.\n\nAdd fimc_is_hw_wait_intmsr0_intmsd0() after mode configuration, ensuring\nhardware state synchronization and stable interrupt handling.", "datePublished": "2025-07-08T09:31:29", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-18T21:31:34", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/b0d92b94278561f43057003a73a17ce13b7c1a1a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e4077a10a25560ec0bd0b42322e4ea027d6f76e2", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bb97dfab7615fea97322b8a6131546e80f878a69", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/14acbb5af101b7bb58c0952949bba4c5fdf0ee7e", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bd9f6ce7d512fa21249415c16af801a4ed5d97b6", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-38237", "https://lists.debian.org/debian-lts-announce/2025/10/msg00007.html"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-38237"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00e5c080-4653-3e43-8c54-80f6790b4c7d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <bd9f6ce7d512fa21249415c16af801a4ed5d97b6"}, {"id": "0ce41f98-7ca5-39c5-a0e0-2d4e61ebe069", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "156942ed-0090-37bf-bc33-119304cd349c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9a761e436843f228eaa2decda6d2c6dbd5ef1480 <14acbb5af101b7bb58c0952949bba4c5fdf0ee7e"}, {"id": "5af734f2-b47f-3a7b-a884-11dba71a964f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "9a761e436843f228eaa2decda6d2c6dbd5ef1480 <bd9f6ce7d512fa21249415c16af801a4ed5d97b6"}, {"id": "658c18e1-0764-3ca0-8538-c16217e729ce",